                          "width": "fill_container",
                          "content": "I.    INTRODUCTION",
                          "fontFamily": "Inter",
                          "fontSize": 13,
                          "fontWeight": "700"
                        },
                        {
                          "type": "text",
                          "id": "hF2vT",
                          "name": "paragraph",
                          "fill": "$text-primary",
                          "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                          "width": "fill_container",
                          "content": "1.    On July 16, 1999, the Inter-American Commission on Human Rights received a petition signed by a group of victims of the terrorist attack perpetrated against the headquarters of the Israeli-Argentinian Mutual Association [Asociación Mutual Israelita Argentina] (AMIA) organized through the Active Memory Civil Association.",
                          "lineHeight": 1.6,
                          "fontFamily": "Inter",
                          "fontSize": 12
                        },
                        {
                          "type": "text",
                          "id": "BxOzI",
                          "name": "sectionTitle2",
                          "fill": "$text-primary",
                          "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                          "width": "fill_container",
                          "content": "II.    PROCEDURE OF THE PETITION BEFORE THE IACHR",
                          "fontFamily": "Inter",
                          "fontSize": 13,
                          "fontWeight": "700"
                        },
                        {
                          "type": "text",
                          "id": "XPB1X",
                          "name": "paragraph2",
                          "fill": "$text-primary",
                          "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                          "width": "fill_container",
                          "content": "2.    The initial petition was presented on July 16, 1999 by the Active Memory Civil Association with the co-sponsorship of the Center for Legal Studies (CELS), the Center for International Law and Justice (CEJIL) and Dr. Alberto Luis Zuppi.",
                          "lineHeight": 1.6,
                          "fontFamily": "Inter",
                          "fontSize": 12
                        }
